name: Ooh La La Dessert Boutique
comment: Free wifi, excellent cupcakes and coffee drinks :)Hours:Mon-Thu 8am-8pmFri-Sat 8am-10pm

name: UNM LGBTQ Resource Center
directions: Enter Building 20A through the courtyard facing Buena Vista Ave. The LGBTQ Resource Center is on the lower level. The single-unit bathroom is room B13.
comment: LGBTQ Resource Center is open 9am-5pm.

name: Lowe's
directions: At front of building

name: La Quinta Inn
directions: off lobby, walk past front desk on left and b-fast area on right, then turn right down hall. Bathroom is immediately on right, across from elevator.

name: Knoebels Amusement Resort
directions: Near the beginning of the park entrance, close to the Giant Wheel, the Skloosh, and the picnic pavilions.
comment: Its a family bathroom with locking single stalls surrounding it.

name: ZaZa Fine Salad And Wood-Oven Pizza Co
directions: Restroom is upstairs near Second-floor dining area.

name: Mestizo Cafe
directions: bathrooms are through the rear door in cafe (just to the right of the counter) and down that hallway.  Cafe is located within City Front Apartment Complex, on South side of street
comment: Cafe would probably prefer that you buy something, but may not notice if you look confidant and walk right in.

name: Utah Pride Center
directions: If you enter through the coffee shop (Cafe Marmalade) and walk towards the back of the building, past the baristas, bathrooms are in the hallway to your right.  There are two gender neutral bathrooms. Alternately, you could walk to the back of the building and enter through the back door directly into the hallway with bathrooms (now to your left)
comment: If you are aged 14-20 there are also two gender neutral bathrooms in the youth drop in space (TINT) across the parking lot.  If you fit that age range, feel free to use.

name: The Vegan House
directions: Enter, order something delicious. Head into the main dining area and the restrooms are in the small hallway in the back.
comment: I'm nearly 100% positive that they are gender neutral. I recall there only being on restroom, and it's single and locking.

name: Truly Vegan Restaurant
directions: Enter, order something. Restrooms through the kitchen; walk into kitchen area and head back until you see a small area with a door on the left. That's the bathroom.
comment: The food here is delicious but a little pricey for a budget, as nearly everything is a la carte. Try something out like the miso soup!

name: B&B Do It Center
directions: Enter through front door, and the restroom is all the way in the back to the right of the \"key desk.\"
comment: There is another restroom marked \"private\" to the left of the key desk behind a display of key accessories that is usually open to the public. The staff here is generally friendly and laid back.

name: Mission Oaks Cafe
directions: Enter, order something (i.e. bagel, coffee). Restroom is in the back, past the waitress station and kitchen, to the right.
comment: The food here isn't worth buying and they have almost no vegetarian/vegan food, so a bagel or a soda is your best bet. Don't forget to leave a modest tip!

name: Vons
directions: Enter through any entrance, turn left, gendered restrooms to the left past the Wells Fargo center and ATM.
comment: Sometimes there are signs posted saying, \"Women's restroom for WOMEN'S use only.\" I think this only happened because a teenage boy peed all over the bathroom once. The sign isn't there any longer.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Enter through front entrance, i.e. not on the patio, walk straight through, single bathrooms to the left.

name: Element Coffee Co.
directions: If entering from Ventura Blvd, which is preferred, go to the register and ask for the bathroom key and then head down a short hallway toward the back exit; bathroom is on the right.
comment: Early morning (6-7 AM) to 10PM. This is a great coffee shop, so try the soy chai latte if you use their toilet.

name: Starbucks
directions: As you walk into the store, there will be a seating area on your left. Directly b ehind that is an open archway where the restrooms are.

name: Dunkin' Donuts
directions: Both bathrooms are at the end of a column of seats and tables to the right as you walk in.

name: University of Missouri-Kansas City
directions: Located on the 1st floor of Royal Hall, near Einstein Bros. coffee.
comment: I prefer to use this restroom, as it is the only gender neutral restroom on the UMKC campus... at least that I'm aware of

name: Tully's Coffee
directions: It's in the back of the store.
comment: I don't think you have to ask for a key... but this place is small enough that they might be pissed if you don't buy something.  I did.

name: Adagia Restaurant
directions: There are two single room unisex bathrooms near the courtyard.
comment: This is a fancy restaurant.  You would only use these restrooms if you were eating there.

name: Rose Garden Branch Library
directions: There is a family bathroom on the second floor, behind the computer lab.
comment: Monday Closed Tuesday 11:00 AM - 8:00 PM Wednesday 11:00 AM - 8:00 PM Thursday 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM Friday 1:00 - 6:00 PM Saturday 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM Sunday Closed

name: Minuteman National Park--Old North Bridge (Monument St. entrance)
directions: Across from parking lot near dirt road leading to bridge/monument. There are two single-stall gendered bathrooms, with a single-stall gender-neutral bathroom in between.

name: Starbucks
directions: The doors are locked by 1 men's key and 1 women's key that are located at the counter where you pick up the coffee you ordered.
comment: Despite the awkward bathroom pass scenario, you don't have to wait in line for the bathroom at least, since the keys are returned to the counter.

name: University of Florida - Dauer Hall
directions: Dauer Hall is on Buckman Dr and Union Rd, north of Pugh Hall and east of Farrior Hall. Several unisex bathrooms located throughout the building, even right between men\\'s and women\\'s restrooms. One of them you can get to if you enter from the parking-lot, the entrance with the sign for the lab, it's on the left as you walk in.
comment: Haven\\'t had a chance to check out the inside of the bathrooms yet, but plan and scoping them out later.

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
directions: There's a back door facing the patio area. Go through this door and the bathrooms will be to the left, if you don't want to actually eat there.
comment: The Women's bathroom is usually clean, but I have not been in the Men's. They're single stall right across from each other so you probably won't get too many looks on your way into either.

name: Quiznos
directions: back of the store.
comment: I felt a little pressured to buy something, but maybe I was just hungry.

name: Timothy's Coffee
directions: At the entrance on Queen and BayKey to get in, bring key into bathroom with you.
comment: They're super nice, didn't seem to mind me using their bathroom a couple times a day haha.

name: Infinitea
directions: Right in the back to the left of the counter.
comment: mon-sat: 8am to 8pmsun: noon to 5pmThere are two single stall restrooms, both marked as gender neutral.  One is marked as accessible.

name: Aroma's Coffeehouse Bakeshop
directions: As you walk in the front door, move left around the pastry case and head toward the back door. The bathroom is on your right.
comment: Very friendly shop and not at all nosey.

name: Necto Night Club
directions: Basement level
comment: Gender neutral on Fridays- \"Pride Night\"

name: OCAD
directions: 3rd floor, Right from the elevator
comment: I didn't ever have problems with security at the front desk, but better to be safe than sorry.

name: Zellars
directions: Right as you come in the store from the front entrance.
comment: It's a family bathroom so beware of that.

name: Black Dog Bakery in Martha's Vineyard
directions: Go all the way to the back of the bakery, past the full-service tables. It's the doorway on the right, leading to two doors, which are two individual genderfree bathrooms. The bathrooms are unlabeled single units.
comment: You should probably buy a pastry or something, as many places on the Vineyard don't like it when people just go into places to use bathrooms.

name: Starbucks in  Center City Macy's
comment: 2 single stall, gender neutral bathrooms

name: Eastgate Mall
directions: Located in the Same area as the gender bathrooms
comment: Itâ€™s a family Bathroom

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Enter Jamba Juice, walk to back of store; restroom.

name: Subway
directions: Enter front door, buy something, get key, head to the furthest reaches of the back of the store and voila, a restroom.

name: The Blvd
directions: Enter, presumably for a concert, by paying or sneaking in. Head straight past the bar and concert room entrance; gendered restrooms on the right.

name: Quizno's
directions: in plain sight!

name: Augusta,Ga/mall/Augusta Mall
directions: In the food court
comment: It's a family bathroom,so anyone can go in

name: Subrosa
directions: Enter, to the right of the book area before the counter.

name: Wegmans
directions: By customer service desk with the rest of the restrooms.
comment: Clean, good soap

name: Ventis
directions: On Court St. between Liberty and Commercial on the right hand side.
comment: Great staff, great food.

name: Cartwright Center, UW- La Crosse
street: corner of Campbell Rd. and State Street
directions: on the second floor.
comment: This building contains the university's cafeteria and various lounges and offices.  It's open in the summer too.  Anyone who looks like they belong on a college campus should have no problem getting in.

name: Nordstrom Dept. store
comment: Family bathroom, in addition to the male and female bathrooms

name: Doodle's Restaurant
directions: 2 silver-doored, locking restrooms located on the outside of the building. they're on the left side if you're looking at the store front.
comment: doodle's is fabulous. thank them!

name: Kaleisia Tea Lounge
directions: In the very back of the store, first/only door on the right.
comment: This is a genderfree, handicap accessible bathroom at the friendly, accepting and warm Kaleisia Tea Lounge. There is a sign at the entrance that says \"No Bathroom\" but that is due to some unfortunate and messy incidents involving homeless persons. It would be nice of you to get a drink while you're there, which I think you'll enjoy. Tea of the month is only $2+tax and smoothies start at about $4. Free parking. If you like boba in your drinks, Kaleisia really knows how it's done. I won't take boba from anywhere else in town. www.thetealounge.com

name: University of South Florida
directions: Basement of the FAO (Faculty Office) building across the hall from the Women's and Gender Studies department's office. See www.usf.edu for a map of campus.
comment: There is a unisex bathroom with 2 sinks, 2 urinals and one handicap accessible stall with a slide lock. The entrance to this bathroom also locks. Another bathroom, adjacent to this one, has one locking handicap accessible stall, but the entrance to the bathroom does not lock. This building is open only from morning to 7pm and parking is not free.

name: Sweet Adeline Bakeshop
directions: Walk to the back, pass the open door to the kitchen on right. Bathroom door is immediately after this, on the right as well.
comment: Best cupcakes ever (but they run out fast)!Hours: Mon-Fri 7am-6pm, Sat & Sun 8am-5pm

name: Whole Foods-Art museum area
directions: next to the cafe seating area next to the registers.
comment: Two single bathrooms w/ locking doors gender neutral.

name: Shoprite
directions: In the back thru the produce. Single locking bathrooms, always deserted.

name: Cosi coffeeshop
directions: In the back, ask for key. Handicapped accessible. Gendered bathrooms but single-person-access
comment: Queer friendly and most employees will let you use it without buying. Or just lie and say you'll get something when you come out.

name: Landmark Saloon
directions: Go in the front door, and go as far straight back as possible.

name: Bauhaus
directions: Back behind the kitchen area
comment: bauhaus has two single stall locking bathrooms, one that has an M and one that has a W but it is very strongly the culture of the regulars to use whatever bathroom is first available/treat them as gender neutral bathrooms, regardless of whatever bathroom people typically use or where they sit on the genderqueer spectrum.just walk right in. you don't have to buy anything. bauhaus employees are some of the nicest people on earth. i go there every day and have only seen them get upset at a customer ONCE, and that's because he was harassing me. i love the bauhaus

name: Dance Home/Santa Monica Power Yoga East
directions: This is a dance/yoga studio above radio shack. The bathrooms are on through the doorway at the far corner of the space from the entrance: two single stalls on your right.
comment: You will feel more comfortable if you are wearing yoga/dance clothes, and possibly if you leave your shoes outside the door in the hallway.

name: Spenard Shell Gas Station
directions: its to the left of the cashier counter between the wall cooler and the atm.

name: Value Village
directions: in the back of the store to the left of the furniture section.

name: Grand Coney
directions: Apart from the set of traditional restrooms near the kitchen, there is a genderfree one back near the ice cream counter. The genderfree restroom is only available during the day although the restaurant is often open all night.

name: Marie Catribs
directions: One locking genderfree bathroom and a locking women's room off an alcove immediately to the right as you enter from the parking lot.
comment: This restaurant is amazing. Everyone is friendly and the food is great, and can be cheap if you pick the right things. Good place for vegan, gluten-free and other food-sensitive people.Hours: M-F 7a-8p, Sat 8a-4p.

name: The Ultra Lounge
directions: In the hallway past the bar. It's a bit cramped back there.
comment: This is a very cool, clean, smoke-free gay bar. They have coffee, beer, wine, and free Pacman in the back.Hours: M-F 8a-12, Sat 8a-2a.

name: The Electric Cheetah
directions: Back wall of a single dining room restaurant, two gender-free locking restrooms. ETA: the bathrooms are now gendered because the restaurant started selling alcohol, but they still lock.
comment: Hours: M-W 11a-9p, Th-Sat 11a-10p, Sun 10a-4p.

name: Caffe de Luca
directions: Midway through the restaurant on the right side are two unisex locking bathrooms.

name: Filter Coffee Shop
directions: Straight ahead after you enter just before the swinging doors to the kitchen are two individually locking bathrooms with no signage at all.

name: Treat
directions: Through the dining room, on your right.
comment: Indian-fusion restaurant, delicious.

name: Urban Beans
directions: 7th St just north of Osborn
comment: Great coffee shop has two single-locking bathrooms that are gender-free. Enjoy!

name: BWI Marshall Airport
directions: BWI Marshall has family restrooms in many locations throughout the terminal building. There are four on Concourse A - one before security between security and the bank, one just past security near the Phillips restaurant, one at gate A9 and one in baggage claim on the lower level.There are five family restrooms in the Concourse B area - one at security, one near the Silver Diner restaurant, one at gate B2, another at gate B7 and one at baggage claim belt 5.Concourse C has two family restrooms - one in the upper level back hallway near the Lost & Found office and one at gate C7.There are four near Concourse D - one is in the upper level back hallway near Bill Bateman's restaurant, one in the back hallway behind the Air Tran Airways ticket counter, another at gate D7 and one at baggage claim belt 12.
comment: i've only used the family bathroom near the M&T Bank, a janitor unlocked the door for me. the door closed automatically (it took a few seconds) and has a manual lock on it. I think the family bathrooms are usually open/available for use but I'm not sure. I don't know which ones are accessible.

name: Blue Moon Coffe Cafe
comment: Really great coffee shop!Knitting group Tuesday evenings.Open 7am-10pm weekdays, and 8am-10pm weekends.

name: Book Barn Downtown
comment: Used bookstore in downtown Niantic, CT. Open 9am - 9pm every day except for Christmas and Thanksgiving. Has a one-person locking genderfree bathroom.

name: PPGLCC Pride Center of Colorado Springs
directions: Located in the back hallway of the center just ask staff working at the entrance and they will help you. Center is located between The Bijou Bar & Grill and Paul's House of Hair on Bijou.
comment: Located in the Pikes Peak Gay and Lesbian Community Center of Colorado Springs PPGLCC- Your Pride Center! Stop in to pee, stay to chat! 2:00pm-6:00pm Monday-Friday

name: Loews Theater
directions: Two locations--both gender-labeled. One is in the lobby that you can access without buying a ticket, to the right of the kiosk (adjacent bathrooms), the other adjacent bathrooms are by the theaters in the back.
comment: They're large bathrooms with locking stalls. They appear pretty gender-safe--you can just walk right into them and take a stall and I don't think there would be a problem. Act confident.

name: Walmart
directions: In the very back, between the shoes and the crafts. Family Bathroom.

name: Canterbury House Chapel and Student Center
directions: There are two bathrooms here with no gender markers. They are large, accessible rooms with a single toilet and sink, and extremely well kept. The first is on your immediate right when you first walk in the front door. The second is around the corner, two rights, near doors that lead to the stairway, lounge, and chapel proper.
comment: A+! :) This is a student center and chapel mainly for Episcopal students of SMU. However, it is open to ALL people. The ministry is (currently) VERY inclusive, LGBTQ+ friendly and knowledgeable.It is only open certain hours, and you might run into the chaplain or students who will want to speak to you, but for the most part anyone there will be friendly and helpful, and okay if all you want to do is pee and get out.More info at:http://www.canterburydallas.org/

name: The Brick & Joe's
directions: There are several toilet locations. The first bathrooms are in the main room, at the back beyond the dancefloor/stage. These ARE gendered bathrooms. The men's room has three urinals and ONE toilet in a stall that locks. I haven't seen the women's.In the second half of the club, there are three gender-free single-stall locking toilets behind the pool table. They have always been clean/well kept when I've been.
comment: The Brick is a gay club geared toward men who like men (especially half naked boys) but very open to all genders. You'll see all kinds here, lots of women, transwomen, drag queens, and a few transmen.Go to:http://www.brickdallas.com/For info on hours, age restrictions, and cover charges.

name: Weisman Art Museum
directions: Bottom floor of building. Take the elevator to the bottom floor.  The restroom is right there, in the foyer. This is under the museum, near the vehicle entrance to the parking ramp.
comment: \"Free access\" to this single- stalled locking \"Employee Bathroom\" if the building is unlocked. From East River Parkway, look for the Weisman Art Museum just south of Washington Avenue bridge. Enter foyer at street level to the right of the vehicle entrance to the parking ramp.  After peeing in restroom, consider attending art museum by taking elevator upstairs.

name: Portland Alano Club
comment: Single stall gendered bathrooms in the basement and first floor.  Genderfree bathrooms on the second floor.

name: Boyds Coffee
comment: mon - fri 6:30am - 5:30pmsaturday - 7am-4pmsunday - closedrestrooms for customers

name: Kafein
directions: Look straight ahead as you enter and go to the back of the cafe.  Bathrooms are behind the counter and to the left.  All are single-occupancy.  Doors marked 'Men?' and 'Women?' are specifically unisex.

name: Western Oregon University
directions: Smith Music Hall by the candy machines in the main hall way of the building.
comment: The Smith Music Hall is closed later in the evening to the public but in general you can go in whenever.

name: Sheetz gas
comment: 24 hours

name: Cole Library
directions: There are two gender neutral (single-stalled & accessible) bathrooms on the third floor of the library.
comment: The library is generally open every day, from 8:00 a.m. to  the afternoon or evening; it is both a public library and a college libraryHere is the website: http://www.colelibrary.org/The college is also currently working on installing gender-neutral bathrooms in other public areas of campus

name: Avenue Bread
directions: Turn right at the end of the counter. The two single occupancy genderfree bathrooms are down the hall on the left side, across from the kitchens.

name: The Atrium in the Arts and Journalism Building at Ball State University
directions: This unisex bathroom is located in the first floor Atrium dining area of the Arts and Journalism Building at Ball State University. If you are in the seating area (looking at the backs of the cashiers), the unisex bathroom is in a small alcove to the right. It is right next to an door that says \\'EMPLOYEES ONLY.\\' However, non-employees are allowed to use the bathroom.
comment: When I used it, it was well-maintained and clean.

name: Cafe Le Delice
comment: The two women that run this place are awesome, as is the food that they serve.  The bathroom is a single person room and unisex, as well as accessible.

name: West Fork
street: 17.5 miles south from Flagstaff or north 9.5 miles from Sedona to about halfway between milepost 385 and 384.
directions: Several unisex toilets near parking lot, all in one shed structure.
comment: http://www.fs.fed.us/r3/coconino/recreation/red_rock/westfork-tr.shtmlFee required to park/use the area.

name: Caked
directions: 2 unisex accessible bathrooms to right of entrance.
comment: Bathrooms specifically for customers only.

name: New Frontiers Natural Market
directions: Southeast corner of building, near cash registers.

name: The LGBT Community Center
directions: Second floor of building; go up the main stairway, make a right at the top of the stairs, and then another right when you hit a wall, door, or something like that. The bathrooms are right there.
